  "prompt": "Do Kit Kat bars have peanut ingredients?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, **standard Kit Kat bars do not contain peanuts**. The classic Kit Kat consists of layers of wafer covered in milk chocolate, without any peanut ingredients. However, Kit Kat offers various flavors and limited-edition versions in different markets worldwide, some of which may include peanut or peanut-flavored ingredients.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n1. **Regional Variations:** Ingredients can vary by country or region. For example, some markets may offer Kit Kat varieties like Peanut Butter Kit Kat or other flavors that include peanut components.\n\n2. **Manufacturing Facilities:** Even if a particular Kit Kat product doesn't list peanuts as an ingredient, it might be manufactured in facilities that handle peanuts. This can pose a cross-contamination risk for individuals with severe peanut allergies.\n\n3. **Packaging Information:** Always check the packaging for the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding ingredients and allergen warnings. Manufacturers may change their recipes or production processes, and labels will provide the necessary details to ensure safety.\n\nIf you have a peanut allergy or are avoiding peanuts for other reasons, it's best to:\n- **Read Labels Carefully:** Look for any mentions of peanuts or peanut derivatives in the ingredient list.\n- **Consult the Manufacturer:** When in doubt, contact the manufacturer directly for detailed information about their products.\n- **Be Cautious with Limited-Edition Flavors:** These may have different ingredients compared to the standard product.\n\nBy taking these precautions, you can enjoy Kit Kat bars safely according to your dietary needs and restrictions.",
